newsitem.title: AUSTRIA: Austrian bonds trudge lower, looking for leads.
newsitem.headline: Austrian bonds trudge lower, looking for leads.

text.p: 1610 GMT - Austrian bonds trudged lower on Thursday in line with Germany, moving in a narrow range amid lack of new leads, traders say.
"German M3 and U.S. jobless figures didn't really come as a surprise," said one, adding that there was little expectation of rate changes in Germany or the U.S. any time soon.
* 10 year benchmark 5.875 pct bond maturing July 2006 down 15 bps at 100.85 to yield 5.75 (5.73) pct in bourse trade, quoted post-market at 100.82/100.92 to yield 5.75/74.
* At the near end, five-year 5.50 percent bond maturing March 2001 down 30 bps at 104.05 to yield 4.46 (4.39) percent in bourse trade, quoted post-market at 104.01/104.11 to yield 4.47/45 percent.
* AGB future up five bps at 108.51 on turnover of 635 lots.
* 10-year spread over Germany down three at two bps, five-year spread up one at five bps.
* Money market rates lower with three-month VIBOR steady at 3.325 and overnight money lower at 2.98/3.23.
